ure context. A mocked/stubbed model can trivially vary output or stay constant, hiding real adaptation failures. This is multi-step agentic behavior. Rejected lower level (Agentic): behavior text explicitly compares successive live attempts after refinement context, i.e., sequenced agentic steps.","test_description":"Run live attempt 1 to failure, capture failure context, run attempt 2 with refinement prompt, and assert implementation content materially differs in failure-relevant regions (not just whitespace).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.28,"Workflow":0.65}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"After 3 failed attempts, service stops and returns structured error containing all three attempts and their test results.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Primary risk is orchestration/bookkeeping correctness across attempts and error shaping across modules. Deterministic stubs can force three failures and expose aggregation/termination bugs. No requirement for real OS/network/subprocess or model-quality evaluation. Rejected higher levels: behavior text is retry-limit/state reporting logic.","test_description":"Use stub generator/test executor that always fails; run orchestrator and assert exactly 3 attempts were made, process terminated, and returned error object includes per-attempt code and test-result details.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"Full non-agentic pipeline wiring works end-to-end with deterministic stubbed model outputs.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior explicitly scopes to non-agentic end-to-end wiring with stubs, so Integration is the intended and sufficient minimum. Unit is too low because full pipeline handoff/attempt bookkeeping must be exercised together. Rejected higher levels: text explicitly disqualifies live model dependence.","test_description":"Run end-to-end service with deterministic model stubs and local test executor, validating generate call flow, test execution, retry bookkeeping, and final outcome object.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.93,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":8,"description":"Full live loop (generate, test, refine, retest) solves at least one known hard function that fails first attempt.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Explicitly a full live multi-step loop with real model behavior and sequential adaptation; this is the definition of Workflow. Agentic alone is too low because single-step model quality does not test iterative pipeline success. Rejected lower levels: stubbed/non-live runs cannot validate this behavior.","test_description":"Execute full production loop with real LLM and real test suite on a curated hard function where first attempt is expected to fail; assert later attempt passes within max attempts and record stepwise outcomes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.01,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.12,"Workflow":0.85}}]}
